|> section
    title=MainSection
    !!disabled=true
    id=main-content
    class=highlight
    !!debug=verbose

This should work - the !!disabled and !!debug lines are commented attributes,
but title, id, and class should still be parsed as valid attributes.

|> subsection
    name=test
    !! hidden=true
    visible=false
    !!count=42
    enabled=true

Testing with spaces after !! - both "!! hidden=true" and "!!count=42" should be comments.

|> mixedcase
    attr1=value1
    !!attr2=commented
    attr3= badspacing
    attr4=ignored

Here attr1 should be valid, attr2 should be commented, but attr3 has bad spacing
so attr3 and attr4 should be treated as plain text.

|> edgecases
    !!empty=
    normal=value
    !!  spaced=test
    !!!triple=exclamation
    key=!!notacomment

Testing edge cases:
- Empty commented value
- Normal attribute after comment
- Multiple spaces after !!
- Triple exclamation marks
- !! in the value (should be normal attribute)

|> validation
    !!valid=comment
    also=valid
    !! another=comment
    still=valid
    bad =space
    shouldbe=plaintext

The "bad =space" line should break attribute parsing, making "shouldbe=plaintext" plain text.

|> onlycomments
    !!all=commented
    !!every=line
    !!is=commented

All lines in this block are commented attributes.

|> regular
    normal=attribute
    another=valid

Back to normal attribute parsing after the commented block.

! This is a regular comment at root level

